001package io.github.ai4ci.example;
002
003import io.github.ai4ci.functions.ImmutableGaussianKernel;
004import io.github.ai4ci.functions.KernelFunction;
005
006/**
007 * A collection of kernels used in example code and tests.
008 *
009 * These kernels are used in the risk model to produce current risk estimates
010 * based on the timing of events such as symptom onset, test sampling and
011 * contact events. They are defined as simple Gaussian kernels with parameters
012 * chosen to produce reasonable shapes for the respective events.
013 *
014 * @author Rob Challen
015 */
016public enum Kernels {
017
018        /** A kernel for symptom onset that peaks around 2 days after infection. */
019        DEFAULT_SYMPTOM_ONSET_KERNEL(
020                        ImmutableGaussianKernel.builder().setMinimum(-3).setMaximum(7).setMu(2)
021                                        .setSigma(3).setSum(5).build()
022        ),
023        /**
024         * A kernel for sampling test results that peaks around 2 days after
025         * infection.
026         */
027        DEFAULT_TEST_SAMPLE_KERNEL(
028                        ImmutableGaussianKernel.builder().setMinimum(-5).setMaximum(11)
029                                        .setMu(2).setSigma(3).setSum(10).build()
030        ),
031        /**
032         * A kernel for sampling contact events that peaks around the time of
033         * infection.
034         */
035        DEFAULT_CONTACT_KERNEL(
036                        ImmutableGaussianKernel.builder().setMinimum(0).setMaximum(10).setMu(0)
037                                        .setSigma(3).setSum(7.5).build()
038
039        );
040
041        private KernelFunction kernel;
042
043        private Kernels(KernelFunction kernel) {
044                this.kernel = kernel;
045        }
046
047        /**
048         * Get the kernel function associated with this enum instance.
049         *
050         * @return a {@link io.github.ai4ci.functions.KernelFunction} used to compute
051         *         risk contributions from events such as symptom onset, test
052         *         sampling and contact events.
053         */
054        public KernelFunction kernel() {
055                return this.kernel;
056        }
057}
